<li id="cite_note-SmithHam-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-SmithHam_3-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-SmithHam_3-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith1836" class="citation journal cs1">Smith, Joseph (April 1836). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.josephsmithpapers.org/paper-summary/letter-to-oliver-cowdery-circa-9-april-1836/2">"For the Messenger and Advocate"</a>. <i>The Latter Day Saints' Messenger and Advocate</i>. <b>2</b> (7): 290. <q>[T]he first mention we have of slavery is found in the Holy Bible, pronounced by a man [Noah] who was perfect in his generation, and walked with God. And so far from that prediction being averse to the mind of God, it remains as a lasting monument of the decree of Jehovah, to the shame and confusion of all who have cried out against the South, in consequence of their holding the sons of Ham in servitude. 'And he said, Cursed be Canaan; a servant of servants shall he be unto his brethren.' ... (Gen. 9:25-26). Trace the history of the world from this notable event down to this day, and you will find the fulfillment of this singular prophecy. [T]he curse is not yet taken off from the sons of Canaan, neither will be until it is affected by as great a power as caused it to come; and the people who interfere the least with the purposes of God in this matter, will come under the least condemnation before Him; and those who are determined to pursue a course which shows an opposition and a feverish restlessness against the designs of the Lord, will learn, when perhaps it is too late for their own good, that God can do his own work without the aid of those who are not dictated by his counsel.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Latter+Day+Saints%27+Messenger+and+Advocate&amp;rft.atitle=For+the+Messenger+and+Advocate&amp;rft.volume=2&amp;rft.issue=7&amp;rft.pages=290&amp;rft.date=1836-04&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.josephsmithpapers.org%2Fpaper-summary%2Fletter-to-oliver-cowdery-circa-9-april-1836%2F2&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+slavery" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-DC134-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-DC134_4-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-DC134_4-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">D&amp;C <a href="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Doctrine_and_Covenants/Section_134#12" class="extiw" title="s:The Doctrine and Covenants/Section 134">Section 134&#58;12</a></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Life_and_Legacy-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Life_and_Legacy_5-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Life_and_Legacy_5-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFFlake1999" class="citation archive">Flake, Joel. "<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://search.lib.byu.edu/byu/record/lee.3073452?holding=ad2wvimxwgpznx6l">Green Flake: His Life and Legacy</a>" (1999) [Textual Record]. Americana Collection, Box: BX 8670.1 .F5992f 1999, p.&#160;8. Provo, Utah: L. Tom Perry Special Collections, Brigham Young University.</cite></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Journal_of_Discourses_10-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Journal_of_Discourses_10_6-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Journal_of_Discourses_10_6-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Journal_of_Discourses_10_6-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Journal_of_Discourses_10_6-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Journal_of_Discourses_10_6-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFYoung1863" class="citation cs1">Young, Brigham (1863). <span class="cs1-ws-icon" title="s:Journal of Discourses/Volume 10/The Persecutions of the Saints, etc."><a class="external text" href="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Journal_of_Discourses/Volume_10/The_Persecutions_of_the_Saints,_etc."><i>Journal of Discourses/Volume 10/The Persecutions of the Saints, etc.</i>&#160;</a></span>. pp.&#160;104–111 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Wikisource" title="Wikisource">Wikisource</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Journal+of+Discourses%2FVolume+10%2FThe+Persecutions+of+the+Saints%2C+etc.&amp;rft.pages=104-111&amp;rft.date=1863&amp;rft.aulast=Young&amp;rft.aufirst=Brigham&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+slavery" class="Z3988"></span></span>
