<li id="cite_note-redd-62"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-redd_62-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-redd_62-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-redd_62-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-redd_62-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation news cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.newspapers.com/newspage/72065072/#id=2719347&amp;offset=1">"Brief History Alex Bankhead and Marinda Redd Bankhead (mention of Dr Pinney of Salem)"</a>. <a href="/wiki/The_Broad_Ax" title="The Broad Ax">The Broad Ax</a>. March 25, 1899.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Brief+History+Alex+Bankhead+and+Marinda+Redd+Bankhead+%28mention+of+Dr+Pinney+of+Salem%29&amp;rft.date=1899-03-25&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newspapers.com%2Fnewspage%2F72065072%2F%23id%3D2719347%26offset%3D1&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+slavery" class="Z3988"></span></span>
