</li>
<li id="cite_note-64"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-64">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFJohn_Todd1906" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/John_Todd_(abolitionist)" title="John Todd (abolitionist)">John Todd</a> (1906). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=eFM0AQAAMAAJ"><i>Early Settlement and Growth of Western Iowa; Or, Reminiscences</i></a>. Historical Department of Iowa. pp.&#160;134–137. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780598279057" title="Special:BookSources/9780598279057"><bdi>9780598279057</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Early+Settlement+and+Growth+of+Western+Iowa%3B+Or%2C+Reminiscences&amp;rft.pages=134-137&amp;rft.pub=Historical+Department+of+Iowa&amp;rft.date=1906&amp;rft.isbn=9780598279057&amp;rft.au=John+Todd&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DeFM0AQAAMAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+slavery" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-gunnison-65"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-gunnison_65-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFJohn_Williams_Gunnison1852" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/John_Williams_Gunnison" title="John Williams Gunnison">John Williams Gunnison</a> (1852). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/mormons00gunngoog"><i>The Mormons: Or, Latter-day Saints, in the Valley of the Great Salt Lake: a History of Their Rise and Progress, Peculiar Doctrines, Present Condition, and Prospects, Derived from Personal Observation, During a Residence Among Them</i></a>. Lippincott, Grambo &amp; Company. p.&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/mormons00gunngoog/page/n153">143</a>. <q>Involuntary labor by negroes is recognized by custom; those holding slaves keep them as part of their family, as they would their wives, without any law on the subject. Negro caste springs naturally from their doctrine of blacks being ineligible to the priesthood</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Mormons%3A+Or%2C+Latter-day+Saints%2C+in+the+Valley+of+the+Great+Salt+Lake%3A+a+History+of+Their+Rise+and+Progress%2C+Peculiar+Doctrines%2C+Present+Condition%2C+and+Prospects%2C+Derived+from+Personal+Observation%2C+During+a+Residence+Among+Them&amp;rft.pages=143&amp;rft.pub=Lippincott%2C+Grambo+%26+Company&amp;rft.date=1852&amp;rft.au=John+Williams+Gunnison&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fmormons00gunngoog&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+slavery" class="Z3988"></span>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-66"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-66">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://historytogo.utah.gov/utah_chapters/pioneers_and_cowboys/slaveryinutah.html">Slavery in Utah</a></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-67"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-67">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFLythgoe1967" class="citation journal cs1">Lythgoe, Dennis L. (Fall 1967). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.proquest.com/openview/136fe4bc7890e0b3acc8c1d6ef7aaf89/">"Negro Slavery and Mormon Doctrine"</a>. <i>Western Humanities Review</i>. <b>21</b> (4): 327 &#8211; via ProQuest.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Western+Humanities+Review&amp;rft.atitle=Negro+Slavery+and+Mormon+Doctrine&amp;rft.ssn=fall&amp;rft.volume=21&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=327&amp;rft.date=1967&amp;rft.aulast=Lythgoe&amp;rft.aufirst=Dennis+L.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.proquest.com%2Fopenview%2F136fe4bc7890e0b3acc8c1d6ef7aaf89%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+slavery" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-68"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-68">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCarter1965" class="citation book cs1">Carter, Kate B. (1965). <i>The Story of the Negro Pioneer</i>. Salt Lake City, Utah: Daughters of Utah Pioneers. <q>We feel it to be our duty to define our position in relation to the subject of slavery. There are several in the Valley of the Salt Lake from the Southern States, who have their slaves with them. There is no law in Utah to authorize slavery, neither any to prohibit it. If the slave is disposed to leave his master, no power exists there, either legal or moral, that will prevent him. But if the slave chooses to remain with his master, none are allowed to interfere between the master and the slave. All the slaves that are there appear to be perfectly contented and satisfied. When a man in the Southern states embraces our faith, the Church says to him, if your slaves wish to remain with you, and to go with you, put them not away; but if they choose to leave you, or are not satisfied to remain with you, it is for you to sell them, or let them go free, as your own conscience may direct you. The Church, on this point, assumes not the responsibility to direct. The laws of the land recognize slavery, we do not wish to oppose the laws of the country. If there is sin in selling a slave, let the individual who sells him bear that sin, and not the Church.<i><a href="/wiki/Millennial_Star" title="Millennial Star">Millennial Star</a></i>, February 15, 1851.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Story+of+the+Negro+Pioneer&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Daughters+of+Utah+Pioneers&amp;rft.date=1965&amp;rft.aulast=Carter&amp;rft.aufirst=Kate+B.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+slavery" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-lizzy_flake-69"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-lizzy_flake_69-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-lizzy_flake_69-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFNicholas_R._Cataldo1998" class="citation web cs1">Nicholas R. Cataldo (1998). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.sbcity.org/about/history/lizzy_flake_rowan___slave.asp">"Former Slave Played Major Role In San Bernardino's Early History: Lizzy Flake Rowan"</a>. City of San Bernardino.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Former+Slave+Played+Major+Role+In+San+Bernardino%27s+Early+History%3A+Lizzy+Flake+Rowan&amp;rft.pub=City+of+San+Bernardino&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.au=Nicholas+R.+Cataldo&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sbcity.org%2Fabout%2Fhistory%2Flizzy_flake_rowan&#95;__slave.asp&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+slavery" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-millennial_star-70"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-millennial_star_70-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation news cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=B5pJAAAAYAAJ">"The Latter-Day Saints' Millennial Star, Volume 17"</a>. 1855. p.&#160;63. <q>Most of those who take slaves there pass over with them in a little while to San Bernardino ... How many slaves are now held there they could not say, but the number relatively was by no means small. A single person had taken between forty and fifty, and many had gone in with smaller numbers.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+Latter-Day+Saints%27+Millennial+Star%2C+Volume+17&amp;rft.pages=63&amp;rft.date=1855&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DB5pJAAAAYAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+slavery" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-71"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-71">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMark_Gutglueck" class="citation news cs1">Mark Gutglueck. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://sbcsentinel.com/2016/07/mormons-created-and-then-abandoned-san-bernardino/">"Mormons Created And Then Abandoned San Bernardino"</a>. San Bernardino County Sentinel.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Mormons+Created+And+Then+Abandoned+San+Bernardino&amp;rft.au=Mark+Gutglueck&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fsbcsentinel.com%2F2016%2F07%2Fmormons-created-and-then-abandoned-san-bernardino%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+slavery" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Gavin-72"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Gavin_72-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCamille_Gavin2007" class="citation book cs1">Camille Gavin (2007). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=foeTAwAAQBAJ"><i>Biddy Mason: A Place of Her Own</i></a>. America Star Books. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781632491909" title="Special:BookSources/9781632491909"><bdi>9781632491909</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Biddy+Mason%3A+A+Place+of+Her+Own&amp;rft.pub=America+Star+Books&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.isbn=9781632491909&amp;rft.au=Camille+Gavin&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DfoeTAwAAQBAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormonism+and+slavery" class="Z3988"></span></span>
